properties.description: Executive Dashboard is for senior managers to monitor performance within their business, giving them both a high level view as well as the ability to drill down into the granular details of the business. In this example, the organization manufactures fast moving consumables, using a reseller model to distribute its products across multiple regions.

loadScript:
///$tab Main
SET ThousandSep=',';
SET DecimalSep='.';
SET MoneyThousandSep=',';
SET MoneyDecimalSep='.';
SET MoneyFormat='$#,##0.00;($#,##0.00)';
SET TimeFormat='h:mm:ss TT';
SET DateFormat='M/D/YYYY';
SET TimestampFormat='M/D/YYYY h:mm:ss[.fff] TT';
SET MonthNames='Jan;Feb;Mar;Apr;May;Jun;Jul;Aug;Sep;Oct;Nov;Dec';
SET DayNames='Mon;Tue;Wed;Thu;Fri;Sat;Sun';

LET vCurrentMonthNum = NUM(Month(Makedate(2013,5,31)));
LET vCurrentMonth = Month(Makedate(2013,5,31));
Let vCurrentYear = num(year(Makedate(2013,5,31)));


Let vTodaysDate = num(makedate(2013,5,31));
Let v12month = num(Makedate(2012,5,31));
Let vRolling12months = Num#($(v12month),'YYYYMM');

LET vOldDate = num(Makedate(2013,5,31));

LET vToday = (Makedate(2013,5,31));

LET vAdjDays = $(vTodaysDate) - $(vOldDate); //the gap between july 2003 and today

SET vQVDPath = "Database\QVD\";

LOAD
    AccountGroup,
    AccountGroupDesc
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/AccountGroupMaster.qvd'
(qvd);




///$tab Account
AccountGroupMaster:
LOAD AccountGroup, 
     AccountGroupDesc
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/AccountGroupMaster.qvd' (qvd);

LOAD AccountGroup, 
     AccountGroupDesc
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/AccountGroupMaster.qvd'
(qvd);

AccountMaster:
LOAD Account, 
     AccountGroup
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/AccountMaster.qvd' (qvd);



///$tab Budget
Budget:
LOAD 
     Region & '_' & Date(Addmonths(Month, 12), 'YYYYMM') as MonthlyRegionKey,
     Budget as [Budget Amount]
FROM
'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/RegionalSales.xlsx'
(ooxml, embedded labels, table is Sheet1);

///$tab Inventory
InventoryBalances:
LOAD "Line Desc 1", 
     ClassTurns, 
     ThroughputQty, 
     CostPrice, 
     StockOH
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/InventoryBalances.qvd' (qvd);
///$tab Product
ItemMaster:
LOAD "Product Group", 
     "Product Line", 
     "Product Sub Group", 
     "Product Type", 
    "Short Name"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ItemMaster.qvd' (qvd);

ProductSubGroupMaster:
LOAD "Product Sub Group", 
     "Product Sub Group Desc"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ProductSubGroupMaster.qvd' (qvd);

ProductTypeMaster:
LOAD "Product Type", 
     "Product Type Desc"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ProductTypeMaster.qvd' (qvd);

ProductGroupMaster:
LOAD "Product Group", 
     "Product Group Desc"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ProductGroupMaster.qvd' (qvd);

ItemBranchMaster:
LOAD "Item-Branch Key", 
     "Short Name"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ItemBranchMaster.qvd'(qvd);

///$tab Sales Rep
SalesRepMaster:
LOAD "Sales Rep", 
     "Sales Rep Name"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/SalesRepMaster.qvd' (qvd);
///$tab FactTable
FactTable:
LOAD 
    Region  & '_' & Date(addmonths(YYYYMM, 12), 'YYYYMM') as MonthlyRegionKey,
    Region,
     "Address Number", 
     CustKey, 
     "Invoice Number", 
     "Item-Branch Key", 
     "Late Shipment", 
     "Line Desc 1", 
     "Open Order Amount", 
     "Order Number", 
     "Order Status", 
     Date(Addmonths(OrderDate, 24)) as OrderDate, 
     OrderID, 
     OrderStat, 
     Addmonths("Promised Delivery Date",24) as "Promised Delivery Date", 
     "Sales Amount", 
     "Sales Cost Amount", 
     "Sales Margin Amount", 
     "Sales Price", 
     "Sales Quantity", 
     "Ship To", 
     Addmonths(YYYYMM, 12) as YYYYMM
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/FactTable.qvd' (qvd);

Expenses:
LOAD 
    Region & '_' & Date(Addmonths(YYYYMM,12), 'YYYYMM') as MonthlyRegionKey,
     Region, 
     Account, 
     Addmonths(YYYYMM, 12) as YYYYMM, 
     ExpenseActual, 
     ExpeenseBudget as ExpenseBudget
FROM
'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/Expenses.xls'
(biff, embedded labels, table is Sheet1$);

CONCATENATE (FactTable) LOAD
    MonthlyRegionKey,
    Region,
    YYYYMM
RESIDENT Expenses;

DROP FIELDS Region, YYYYMM FROM Expenses;

HistoryFlag:
LOAD DISTINCT
    YYYYMM,
    if(YYYYMM <= monthstart($(vTodaysDate)), 1, 0) as _HistoryFlag
RESIDENT FactTable;
    
Accounts:
LOAD 
     Account, 
     AccountDesc
FROM
'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ExpenseAccounts.xls'
(biff, embedded labels, table is Sheet1$)
WHERE AccountDesc > 0;

///$tab Customer
CustomerAddressMaster:
LOAD "Address Number", 
     "Customer Address 1", 
     "Zip Code"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/CustomerAddressMaster.qvd' (qvd);
Directory;

CustomerMap:
LOAD CustKey, 
     CustKeyAR
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/CustomerMap.qvd' (qvd);

CustomerMaster:
LOAD "Address Number", 
     "Business Family", 
     Segment, 
     Customer, 
     "Customer Number", 
     "Customer Type", 
     "Distribution Channel Mgr", 
     Division, 
     Phone, 
     "Region Code", 
     "Regional Sales Mgr", 
     "Zone Mgr", 
     "Sales Rep"
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/CustomerMaster.qvd' (qvd);

ChannelMaster:
LOAD Segment, 
     SegmentDesc, 
     SegmentGroup
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ChannelMaster.qvd' (qvd);
///$tab Calendar
Calendar:
LOAD 
    "Fiscal Quarter", 
     "Fiscal Year"+1 AS "Fiscal Year", 
     Month(addmonths(YYYYMM, 12)) as FiscalMonth, 
     Num(Month(addmonths(YYYYMM,12))) as FiscalMonthNum, 
     FiscalRollQt, 
     addmonths(YYYYMM, 12) as YYYYMM
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/Calendar.qvd' (qvd);
///$tab AR
ARSummary:
LOAD CustKeyAR, 
     ARGross, 
     AROpen, 
     ARCurrent, 
     "AR1-30", 
     "AR31-60", 
     "AR60+", 
     ARCredit, 
     ARSalesPerDay, 
     ARAvgBal
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ARSummary.qvd' (qvd);

[ARSummary-1]:
LOAD CustKeyAR, 
     ARAge, 
     ARAgeBal
FROM 'lib://Executive Dashboard Data/ARSummary-1.qvd' (qvd);

qMetaDef.title: KPI Dashboard
qMetaDef.description: The KPI Dashboard provides a high-level overview of the company in three areas: expenses, revenue and account receivables.

qStringExpression.qExpr: 'Expenses vs. Target  =  ' & num(sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(vYTDYear)}, _HistoryFlag={1}>} ExpenseActual)/sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(vYTDYear)}, _HistoryFlag={1}>} ExpenseBudget), '#,##0%')

'Revenue vs Last Year Revenue = '& num(Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(=vYTDYear)}, FiscalMonthNum={"<=$(vCurrentMonthNum)"}>}[Sales Price]*[Sales Quantity])/Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(=(vYTDYear)-1)}, FiscalMonthNum={"<=$(vCurrentMonthNum)"}>}[Sales Price]*[Sales Quantity]), '#,##0%')
'Account Receivable Overdue  =  ' & num((Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(vYTDYear)}>} AROpen)-Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(vYTDYear)}>} ARCurrent))/Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(vYTDYear)}>} AROpen), '#,##0%')

qMetaDef.title: Account Receivable Analysis
qMetaDef.description: The Account Receivables Analysis sheet provides sales information and a look at the amount due and days sales outstanding for customers.

qProperty.title: Avg Sales Per Day vs AR Avg Balance

qMetaDef.title: Sales Analysis
qMetaDef.description: The Sales Analysis sheet allows the user to monitor the company's revenue to ensure it is on target for the year.

qProperty.title: Sales vs Margin by Sales Rep

qStringExpression.qExpr: 'Total Revenue by Product Group = ' & num(Sum([Sales Quantity]*[Sales Price]), '$#,##0')

qMetaDef.title: Margin Analysis by Sales Rep
qMetaDef.description: This story provides an analysis of sales reps with low margin and sales reps with high margin sales and the top product sold in each group.

style.text: Sales Reps with high margin sales also achieve high revenues. The top products that they sell are Fresh Vegetables, Bologna, Fresh Fruits, and Hot Dog products.

Although Sales Reps with low margin sales have more higher revenue products, they still could not achieve the same margin %. As it is displayed on the revenue bar chart, the top product that is being sold by these sales reps is Hot Dogs. We should consider increasing the margin % on this product.

qMeasure.qDef: if(GetSelectedCount([Fiscal Year])<>1,  	Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(=max([Fiscal Year]))} >} ExpenseActual)/1000, 	Sum({<[Fiscal Year]={$(vYear)}>} ExpenseActual)/1000)

qMetaDef.title: On Time Delivery

qMetaDef.title: CY Sales
